programme.desc:

A danger to the planet that remains largely underestimated. Invasive species, whether animal or plant, are a threat to both biodiversity and the economy. In Belgium, these super champions come by many names: Asian hornets, tiger mosquitoes, giant hogweed, Japanese knotweed, racoons... A report by Samy Hosni for "#Investigation", the RTBF magazine programme.
Guest: Samy Hosni, journalist with RTBF.
Presented by: Dominique Laresche.

programme.title: Échappées belles
programme.desc:
The Cévennes, back to nature
The Cévennes, a land that has all you could wish for. This unspoilt region covers four mountain massifs: Mont Lozère, the Causse-Méjean limestone plateau, the Cévenole valleys and Mont Aigoual. Of France's eleven national parks, it is the only one that's inhabited, offering remarkable landscapes shaped by man and nature.
